Memo - Exploring post-1935 exposure data

Purpose

The goal of this notebook is to explore initial exposure data for HOLC neighborhoods across the U.S. for wells with production dates on or after 1/1/1935 (approximately the time of HOLC grading).

Cities

There were 198 cities in the HOLC dataset. Of these, 57 had wells that were drilled or in operation after 1935 within 1 km a HOLC-graded neighborhood. Of these, 27 had at least 10 wells.

Table. Number of wells within 1 km of graded neighborhoods

Wells

A total of 745062 wells had a spud date, completion date, and/or production start or end date after 1935 (and excluded wells with production dates before 1935.)

Unit of observation is the neighborhood

Exposure to injection wells

Only 1 neighborhood had an injection well within 1 km and 29 had at least one well within 3 km. Ill exclude injection wells for the pre-1935 analyses.

Exposure to producing wells

Producing wells were defined as wells with > 0 BOE of oil and/or gas production, as reported in the Enverus dataset.
